test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 1 == 6
 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod

 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x77bc1d8bdb00> = [[1, 6], [1, 6, 1], [6], [6, 1], [1, 6], [1, 6, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x77bc1d8bdb00>([1, 6])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x77bc1d8bdb00> = [[1, 6], [1, 6, 1], [6], [6, 1], [1, 6], [1, 6, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x77bc1d8bdb00>([6, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x77bc1d8bdb00> = [[1, 6], [1, 6, 1], [6], [6, 1], [1, 6], [1, 6, 1], ...].count
